"title": "8447: hospitality, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8447: hospitality, examples of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture provides many examples of friendship and generosity towards strangers, and encourages believers to be hospitable in turn.</p>\n<h2>Examples of hospitality in the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:2-Gen18:5\">GEN 18:2–18:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:1-Gen19:3\">GEN 19:1–19:3</a> <em>Lot entertains visitors from God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:22-Gen24:25\">GEN 24:22–24:25</a> <em>Abraham's servant is welcomed in Rebekah's home</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:20\">EXO 2:20</a> <em>Moses is welcomed by a priest of Midian</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:15\">JDG 13:15</a> <em>Manoah receives the angel of the LORD.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:1-Judg19:4\">JDG 19:1–19:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:20-Judg19:21\">JDG 19:20–19:21</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam17:27-2Sam17:29\">2SA 17:27–17:29</a> <em>hospitality shown to David and his people</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:7-1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:7–17:16</a> <em>The widow of Zarephath cares for Elijah despite her poverty</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:8-2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:8–4:10</a> <em>a Shunammite provides for Elisha</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:17\">NEH 5:17</a> <em>Nehemiah shows hospitality to fellow Jews.</em></p>\n<h2>Hospitality shown to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10\">MAT 9:10</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15\">MRK 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a> <em>Jesus Christ received hospitality from people of all social backgrounds.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:14-Matt8:15\">MAT 8:14–8:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:29-Mark1:31\">MRK 1:29–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:38-Luke4:39\">LUK 4:38–4:39</a> <em>at Peter's house</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:7\">MAT 26:6–26:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:1-John12:3\">JHN 12:1–12:3</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36\">LUK 7:36</a> <em>at the house of Simon the Pharisee</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:38\">LUK 10:38</a> <em>at the home of Mary and Martha</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:1\">LUK 14:1</a> <em>at the house of a prominent Pharisee</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:5-Luke19:7\">LUK 19:5–19:7</a> <em>at Zacchaeus' house</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:29\">LUK 24:29</a> <em>with disciples in Emmaus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:2\">JHN 2:2</a> <em>at the wedding at Cana</em></p>\n<h2>Hospitality assisted the mission of the apostles</h2>\n<h3>Hospitality shown to the disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:11-Matt10:12\">MAT 10:11–10:12</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:10\">MRK 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:4\">LUK 9:4</a> <em>Jesus Christ sends out the Twelve.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:5-Luke10:7\">LUK 10:5–10:7</a></p>\n<h3>Hospitality shown to Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:32\">ACT 10:32</a> <em>at the home of Simon the tanner</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:48\">ACT 10:48</a> <em>with Cornelius and his family</em></p>\n<h3>Hospitality shown to Paul and his companions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a> <em>at the home of Lydia</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:34\">ACT 16:34</a> <em>at the house of the Philippian jailer</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:2-Acts18:3\">ACT 18:2–18:3</a> <em>with Aquila and Priscilla in Corinth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:8\">ACT 21:8</a> <em>at the house of Philip</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:16\">ACT 21:16</a> <em>at the home of Mnason in Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:2\">ACT 28:2</a> <em>on Malta</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:7\">ACT 28:7</a> <em>at the home of Publius</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:23\">ROM 16:23</a> <em>with Gaius</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:22\">PHM 1:22</a> <em>as a guest of Philemon</em></p>\n<h2>Christians opened their homes for gatherings of believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:19\">1CO 16:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:3-Rom16:5\">ROM 16:3–16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:15\">COL 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:2\">PHM 1:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of inhospitable behaviour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:10-1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:10–25:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:18\">NUM 20:18</a> <em>Edom</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:21-Num21:23\">NUM 21:21–21:23</a> <em>Sihon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:3-Deut23:4\">DEU 23:3–23:4</a> <em>Ammonites and Moabites</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:15\">JDG 19:15</a> <em>Gibeah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:52-Luke9:53\">LUK 9:52–9:53</a> <em>a Samaritan village</em></p>",
